(g) for declaratory decrees except in making a declaration under
paragraph 65(5)(b) and interpleader proceedings under
section 73;
(h) for the issue or revocation of grants of representation of the
estates of deceased persons or the administration or
distribution thereof;
(i) wherein the legitimacy of any person is in question;
*(j) wherein the guardianship or custody of infants is in question;
and
(k) except as specifically provided in any written law for the time
being in force, wherein the validity or dissolution of any
marriage is in question.
